	<title>Subsequences: Examples</title>
	<showme>
		<statement>
			<para>Given the sequence <latex magnify="yes">(a_n := \tfrac{1}{n+1})</latex>, write out the subsequence of even indexed sequence elements.</para>
		</statement>
		<answer type="Solution">
			<para>We have</para>
			<table align="center" border="3" bordercolor="Maroon" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="3">
				<row>
					<cell align="center"><para><latex>n</latex></para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>0</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>1</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>2</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>3</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>4</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>5</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>6</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>7</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>8</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>9</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>10</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>...</para></cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell align="center"><para><latex magnify="yes">a_n</latex></para></cell>
					<cell  align="center"><para>1</para></cell>
					<cell  align="center"><para>1/2</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>1/3</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>1/4</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>1/5</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>1/6</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>1/7</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>1/8</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>1/9</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>1/10</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>1/11</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>...</para></cell>
				</row>
			</table>
			<para>Therefore the subsequence of even indexed sequence elements is</para>
			<math.display>
				<latex>b_i = a_{n_i} = a_{2i}</latex>
			</math.display>
			<para>in tabular form:</para>
			<table align="center" border="3" bordercolor="Maroon" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="3">
				<row>
					<cell align="center"><para><latex>i</latex></para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>0</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>1</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>2</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>3</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>4</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>5</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>6</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>7</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>8</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>9</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>10</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>...</para></cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell align="center"><para><latex magnify="yes">b_i=a_{2i}</latex></para></cell>
					<cell  align="center"><para>1</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>1/3</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>1/5</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>1/7</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>1/9</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>1/11</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>1/13</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>1/15</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>1/17</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>1/19</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>1/21</para></cell>
					<cell align="center"><para>...</para></cell>
				</row>
			</table>
		</answer>
	</showme>
	
	
	
	<showme>
		<statement>
			<para>Given the sequence <latex magnify="yes">(a_n = n)</latex>, find the subsequence corresponding to the function</para>
			<math.display>
				<latex>n\from \NNr \longrightarrow \NNr,\quad n(i):= i^2</latex>
			</math.display>
		</statement>
		<answer type="Solution">
			<para>The required subsequence is</para>
			<math.display>
				<latex magnify="yes">(b_i) = (a_{n(i)}) = (a_{i^2} = i^2)</latex>
			</math.display>
